<br>
Tireless, even as low as at level 1 is priceless. The amount regenerated is not huge, but the real advantage of the skill is that its allow you to regenerate stamina (albeit at a slow rate) in circumstances when you normally don't regenerate AT ALL, namely fighting and especially running. So when travelling, running all over Briefine and Emain, you slowly refresh your stamina pool, almost reducing to zero (with purity of mind and heals available) the time you have to spend sitting, in an environment when you are vulnerable to stealth attacks and need moving wuickly.<br>
<br>
Not parsed Serenity or anything, but at level 1, my &quot;gut feeling&quot; is that it helps quite a bit reducing downtime. The extra amount of time between the time I am at full health and the time I am at full power after a PvE fight seems reduced. Not tested scientifically, so take with a grain of salt, but I like it.<br>
